quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Merciful-to-all
  55,2,taught the Qur'an
  55,3,created man
  55,4,taught him articulate speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon run on precise calculations
  55,6,The stars and the trees submit to Him
  55,7,"The skies, He raised high and has established the balance"
  55,8,That you may not transgress in the balance
  55,9,"but weigh with justice, and do not violate the balance"
  55,10,"The earth, He laid out for all living creatures"
  55,11,"In it are fruits, and date-palms in clusters"
  55,12,And grains on flourishing stems and fragrant plants
  55,13,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,14,"He created Humankind from dry clay, ringing like pottery"
  55,15,And He created the jinn from a fusion of fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,17,He is Lord of the two sunrises and Lord of the two sunsets
  55,18,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,19,"He merged the two seas, converging together"
  55,20,with a barrier they do not over run between them
  55,21,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,22,From out of both comes pearl and coral
  55,23,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny
  55,24,"His are all floating objects, raised above the sea like mountain peaks"
  55,25,So which of your Lord's blessings will you deny